OL,3,CAssisted dying could be legal on Isle
OL,4,Cof Man by 2027 after delay rejected
OL,6,FMHKs were urged to reject the
OL,7,Freferendum by campaigners to ensure
OL,8,F"dying people in the Isle of Man do
OL,9,Fnot have to wait any longer for choice
OL,10,Fand control at the end of their
OL,11,Flives", group Dignity in Dying said.
OL,13,FSarah Wootton, Chief of Executive of
OL,14,Fthe campaign group, said: "The
OL,15,Fdecision sends a clear message that
OL,16,Fdying people don't have time to wait
OL,17,Ffor a safe and compassionate law that
OL,18,Fgives them the choices they need.
