OL,3,CAssisted dying could be legal on Isle
OL,4,Cof Man by 2027 after delay rejected
OL,6,F"The flawed referendum amendment was a
OL,7,Fclear attempt by opponents to delay
OL,8,Fthe Bill's introduction and cause
OL,9,Ffurther unnecessary suffering to dying
OL,10,Fpeople and their families.
OL,12,F"Polling has shown strong public
OL,13,Fsupport for assisted dying. Today's
OL,14,Fdebate has moved that one step closer."
OL,16,FThe proposed legislation has been
OL,17,Fdebated by the House of Keys where
OL,18,Ftopics including the wording of the
OL,19,Flaw, the medication and parameters of
OL,20,Fuse were discussed.
